<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1127,1081,1233]" pageId="12" pageNumber="669">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,211,1081,1105]" pageId="12" pageNumber="669">Note.</emphasis>
It is questionable if 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": COBOS" authorityYear="1972" box="[438,589,1082,1105]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="669" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysifrons">
<emphasis box="[438,589,1082,1105]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="669">A. chrysifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is really from 
<collectingCountry box="[752,819,1081,1105]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="669">Brasil</collectingCountry>
. Kerremans described many species with the same or very similar locality data: “ 
<collectingCountry box="[712,780,1113,1137]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="669">Brésil</collectingCountry>
, Manufacturé de Tabac”. At that time tobacco was transported to 
<collectingCountry box="[504,568,1145,1169]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="669">Brasil</collectingCountry>
from various parts of north-east South America for processing before transport to Europe.
</paragraph>
